race.comment: The well-related NEGOTIATIONS (2) (half to G2 winner Hidden Motive) has been knocking on the door of another victory with five consecutive top-four finishes and strikes a winnable contest here. Is a two-time winner over this sprint journey and gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim. Rates the testing material. TEN GOOD REASONS (4) also hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner and 2xG1 placed Osipenko) and the form he showed when last in work was good enough for a contest of this nature. Can run a race while fresh. HEARTS ARE BETTER (5) is first-up but has a win and a second from two fresh attempts and has tuned up for this, winning two recent trials. Has to be included. EXPRESS CODE (9) has plenty of upside and makes some appeal.
